# any notes.  these are not printed in the final dictionary
@NOTES=
The typical hash function is the xor of the representation of
characters, that is,
$h(c) = \oplus<sup>n</sup><sub>i=1</sub> c<sub>i</sub>$.
</p>

<p>
The tables may be filled with random values or may have values chosen
to avoid {collisions} or for other properties.
</p>

<p>
For games, e.g. chess, "characters" are pieces, like pawn, knight, and
queen.

